<task id="task_gfj_ssv_yq">
    <title>Configuring a Directory Origin</title>
    <shortdesc>Configure a Directory origin to read data from files in a directory. When you
        configure a Directory, you define general properties, including the data format to process.
        Then, you define post-processing options and the properties specific to the data
        format.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <context/>
        <steps id="steps_tvn_b5v_yq">
            <step conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusableSteps.dita#task_kzs_5vz_sq/Step_NameDesc">
                <cmd/>
            </step>
           
            <step>
                <cmd>On the <uicontrol>Files</uicontrol> tab, configure the following
                        properties:<draft-comment author="Loretta">review step above and table.
                    </draft-comment></cmd>
                <info>
                    <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_tm4_vck_5q">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.2*"/>
                            <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="2*"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>File Property</entry>
                                    <entry>Description</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Name</entry>
                                    <entry>Stage name.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Description</entry>
                                    <entry>Optional description.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Data Format</entry>
                                    <entry>Data format for source files. Use one of the following
                                            formats:<ul id="ul_y1t_wql_5q">
                                            <li>Log data</li>
                                            <li>JSON data</li>
                                            <li>Delimited data</li>
                                            <li>XML data</li>
                                        </ul></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Directory</entry>
                                    <entry>A directory local to the <ph
                                            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                                        /> where source files are stored.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>File Name Pattern <xref
                                            href="Directory_FNamePattern.dita#concept_bxt_ndl_5q">
                                            <image href="../Graphics/icon_moreInfo.png" scale="12"
                                                id="image_c4p_p5v_yq"/></xref>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry>Regular expression that describes the file names. For
                                        example, *.log.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Max Files in Directory</entry>
                                    <entry>
                                        <p>The maximum number of files that match the file name
                                            pattern that are allowed in the directory. When the
                                            directory contains more files, the pipeline fails.</p>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>First File to Process <xref
                                            href="Directory_FirstFile.dita#concept_ltv_r3l_5q">
                                            <image href="../Graphics/icon_moreInfo.png" scale="12"
                                                id="image_e4p_p5v_yq"/></xref>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry>Name of the first file to process. Use a name that uses
                                        the file name pattern. <p>When you enter a file name,
                                            Directory reads the first file and other files in the
                                            directory with ascending names.</p></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>File Wait Timeout (secs) <xref
                                            href="Directory_FileWaitTime.dita#concept_fqb_x1l_5q">
                                            <image href="../Graphics/icon_moreInfo.png" scale="12" id="image_h4p_p5v_yq"/></xref>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry>Number of seconds to wait for a new file. If a new file
                                        does not arrive within the specified time, Directory sends
                                        an empty batch to destinations.</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>On the <uicontrol>Post Processing</uicontrol> tab, configure the following
                    properties:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_sgn_dvv_yq">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.2*"/>
                            <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="2*"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Post Processing Property</entry>
                                    <entry>Description</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Error Directory</entry>
                                    <entry>The directory for files that were not completely
                                        processed due to data handling errors.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>File Post-Processing</entry>
                                    <entry>The action taken after processing a file: <ul
                                            id="ul_wsr_h4l_5q">
                                            <li><uicontrol>None</uicontrol> - Leaves the file
                                                alone.</li>
                                            <li><uicontrol>Archive</uicontrol> - Moves the file to
                                                the archive directory.</li>
                                            <li><uicontrol>Delete</uicontrol> - Deletes the
                                                file.</li>
                                        </ul></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Archive Directory</entry>
                                    <entry>The directory for processed files. Available when you
                                        select Archive for the File Post Processing
                                        property.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Archive Retention Time (mins)</entry>
                                    <entry>Number of minutes processed files are saved in the
                                        archive directory. Use 0 to keep the archived files
                                        indefinitely.</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>For log data, on the <uicontrol>Log Data</uicontrol> tab, configure the
                    following properties:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_LogData">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.2*"/>
                            <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="2*"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Log Data Property</entry>
                                    <entry>Description</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Maximum Line Length</entry>
                                    <entry>Maximum number of characters allowed for a line. Longer
                                        lines are truncated.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Use Truncated Flag</entry>
                                    <entry>Adds a boolean field to the record to indicate if a
                                        record was truncated. The field name is Truncated. Possible
                                        values are True for a truncated record and False for
                                        untruncated values.</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>For JSON data, on the <uicontrol>JSON Data</uicontrol> tab configure the
                    following properties:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <table
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusableTables.dita#concept_wfr_rnw_yq/table_JSONdata"
                        id="table_q1r_znw_yq">
                        <tgroup cols="cols_vyq_znw_yq">
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry/>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>For Delimited data, on the <uicontrol>Delimited Data</uicontrol> tab, configure
                    the following properties:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_DelimitedData">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.2*"/>
                            <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="2*"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Delimited Data Property</entry>
                                    <entry>Description</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>File Type</entry>
                                    <entry>File type. Use one of the following options: <ul
                                            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/ul_delFileTypes"
                                            id="ul_zf2_n4w_yq">
                                            <li/>
                                        </ul></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Header Line</entry>
                                    <entry>Indicates whether a file contains a header line.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Convert to Map</entry>
                                    <entry>Converts a file to a map based on the fields in the
                                        header. If no header exists, uses column numbers to map the
                                        fields.</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>For XML data, on the <uicontrol>XML Data</uicontrol> tab, configure the
                    following properties:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_b5x_nbw_yq">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.2*"/>
                            <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="2*"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>XML Data Property</entry>
                                    <entry>Description</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Element Record Delimiter</entry>
                                    <entry>XML element that acts as a record delimiter. </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Maximum Record Length</entry>
                                    <entry>Maximum length for a record. Longer records are
                                        discarded.</entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
